Environment.CurrentDirectory = Path.GetTempPath();

Directory.CreateDirectory("foo");

// This should succeed even on macOS and Windows, but throws an exception.
// System.DirectoryInfo.MoveTo() exhibits the same symptom.
Directory.Move("foo", "FOO");
```

Additionally: Even if the source and destination are _truly_ identical, it is arguably more sensible to apply _desired-state logic_ and perform a quiet no-op rather than throwing an exception.

